would continue as host of the show for 12 years. He has also served as station announcer for [[WFLX-TV]] FOX 29 in [[West Palm Beach, Florida]].{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\n==Voice over==\nShotgun Tom's voice is featured in the motion picture ''[[D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu (2006 film)|D\u00e9j\u00e0 Vu]]'', starring [[Denzel Washington]], and on ''[[America's Most Wanted]]'' and [[Spike TV]]'s ''[[1000 Ways to Die]]''.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nTom also did voice work for his hometown [[San Diego Chargers]]. Tom's voice could be heard on the [[Jumbotron]] during Chargers home games.<ref>[http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/2015/aug/24/shotgun-tom-kelly-k-earth-101-radio-chargers-dj \"Radio won't be same without Shotgun Tom\"], ''San Diego Union Tribune''; accessed February 19, 2018.</ref>\n\nKelly's voice is heard on [[Fred Falke]]'s song \"Radio Days\".<ref>[http://earmilk.com/2015/11/06/fred-falke-returns-with-radio-days-featuring-la-radio-icon-shotgun-tom-kelly Fred Falke returns with 'Radio Days' featuring LA radio icon Shotgun Tom Kelly\"], earmilk.com, November 6, 2015.</ref>\n\n==Hollywood Walk of Fame==\nOn April 30, 2013, \"Shotgun Tom\" Kelly was honored with a Star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame.<ref>[http://www.walkoffame.com/shotgun-tom-kelly \"Shotgun Tom Kelly on the Hollywood Walk of Fame\"], walkoffame.com; accessed February 19, 2018.</ref> His star is located adjacent to another K-Earth personality, The Real [[Don Steele]].<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H6hb3RgM55w|title=\"SHOTGUN TOM\" KELLY HONORED WITH HOLLYWOOD WALK OF FAME STAR|date=May 5, 2013|work=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://shotguntomkelly.com/ \"Shotgun Tom\" Kelly's official website]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/ShotgunTom/ \"Shotgun Tom\" Kelly's Facebook page]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150905133435/http://kearth101.cbslocal.com/show/shotgun-tom-kelly/ KEARTH 101's Page]\n\n{{DEFAU